Project Title: Interactive Portfolio Website
Project Description:
Create a personal portfolio website that showcases your skills, projects, and contact information. Add interactive JavaScript elements such as a navigation menu, a dynamic "Projects" section, and a working contact form.

Features to Include:


1. Navigation Bar (HTML + CSS + JavaScript):
HTML: Create a navigation bar with links to "Home," "About Me," "Projects," and "Contact."
CSS: Style it with a sticky header.
JavaScript: Add smooth scrolling to the section when a user clicks a navigation link.


2. Hero Section (HTML + CSS):
A large header section with your name, a short description, and a "Learn More" button.
Use CSS to add a gradient background or a hero image.


3. Projects Section (HTML + JavaScript):
Display projects as cards.
JavaScript: Add a "View Details" button on each project card that shows more information when clicked.



4. Light/Dark Mode Toggle (CSS + JavaScript):
Create a toggle button to switch between light and dark themes.
JavaScript: Update the class on the body to apply different CSS styles.


5. Contact Form (HTML + JavaScript):
Create a simple form with fields for Name, Email, and Message.
JavaScript: Add form validation to ensure all fields are filled and email is valid.
Optionally, display a "Thank You" message after submission.


6. Footer Section (HTML + CSS):
Include links to your social media profiles styled with CSS.

Technical Requirements:
HTML:
Use semantic elements such as <header>, <main>, <section>, <footer>.
Organize the code with proper indentation and comments.
CSS:
Use Flexbox or Grid for layout.
Apply transitions or animations for hover effects.
Include responsive design using media queries.
